title: 16-Year-Old Steps Into Wind Tunnel To Perform Amazing ‘Sky Dance’ Floating In Air
text:
16-Year-Old Steps Into Wind Tunnel To Perform Amazing ‘Sky Dance’ Floating In Air Subscribe to Reshareworthy! It's FREE and always will be! 
Have you ever heard of sky dancing? It’s part gymnastics, modern dance and indoors sky diving all rolled into one. 
Competitors go into a vertical wind tunnel and much like a skydiver, the person inside is buoyed in the air. Wearing an aerodynamic suit and helmet, they can perform any number of gymnastic moves while floating in the air! 
There are actually sporting events held all over the world and at the Wind Games, 16-year-old Maja Kuczyńska performed her “sky dance” freestyle music routine to Sia’s Chandelier. 
From the moment she steps into the wind tunnel you’ll see why this video is going viral!
